 the Internal Revenue Service for 35 years before his retirement; andWhereas, After his retirement, Paul decided to further contribute to his community by starting his own business called Hofe's Well Drilling, which he successfully ran for 50 years; andWhereas, Paul was a member of the National Groundwater Association and was also the former director and president of the South Atlantic Well Drillers Jubilee; andWhereas, Paul was an active advocate for well regulations and worked closely with the State Health Department concerning said regulations; andWhereas, Paul generously donated wells to Poor House Farm Park, the Berkeley County Youth Fair Land, and local churches in the eastern panhandle of West Virginia; andWhereas, He continued this generosity by drilling wells for many families in West Virginia who would otherwise not have been able to afford the service; andWhereas, Paul also sponsored the Hedgesville Little League team as well as the Hedgesville High School basketball and baseball teams for many years; andWhereas, Paul was seen as a dependable leader to the people of Berkeley County and supported his community; andWhereas, Paul passed away due to Alzheimer's Disease on March 5, 2019, after a lifetime of service to his country, state, and community; therefore, be itResolved by the Legislature of West Virginia:That the Division of Highways change the name of Bridge Number: 02-009/00-002.54  () (02A176), (39.57445, -78.03742) locally known as Johnsontown Bridge, carrying WV 009 over Tilhance Creek in Berkeley County, to the "Paul J. Hofe Memorial Bridge" and, be it Further Resolved, That the Division of Highways is hereby requested to have made and be placed signs identifying the bridge as the " Paul J. Hofe Memorial Bridge",  and, be itFurther Resolved, That the Clerk of the House forward a copy of this resolution to the Commissioner of the Division of Highways. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roste